  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting the CSA in building a robust early warning, preparedness and response-planning mechanism to shocks affecting food security and nutrition in Mauritania, as part of an national Adaptive Social Protection system and as a contribution to an overall DRR scheme.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Action A: Man made crisis and natural disasters,Action C: DIPECHO</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In a context characterized by structural vulnerability and recurrent shocks, and in line with national priorities, WFP intends to operate a strategic shift over the next five years taking on a leading role in supporting Mauritania towards the establishment of an Adaptive Social Protection (ASP) system.Specifically - and in line with the HIP 2019 technical orientations - the present multidonor action aims to support the Government&apos;s efforts to setup a national scheme linking early warning, preparedness, planning and response to shocks affecting food security and nutrition. Such a scheme is an essential prerequisite to reinstate government leadership and ensure food and nutrition assistance can be provided in the most coherent, predictable and timely way possible. Its responsibility falls under the Commissariat &#xE0; la S&#xE9;curit&#xE9; Alimentaire (CSA) and its technical arm the Observatoire de la S&#xE9;curit&#xE9; Alimentaire (OSA).The action - implemented by WFP in partnership with ACF and Oxfam - will aim to achieve two complementaryresults:Result 1: The CSA and other national institutions&apos; capacities, tools and processes for early warning, preparedness and response planning to shocks affecting food security and nutrition are strengthened, in turn providing a common framework to enhance the relevance, reactiveness and consistency of partners&apos; interventions.Result 2: The early warning system&apos;s Community Sentinel Site and pastoral monitoring mechanisms are designed and gradually piloted, as a mean to ensure that information produced locally can be consolidated, flow upwards, and be given due consideration to inform national responses to shocks affecting food security and nutrition.</narrative>
  </description>
